<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moore</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-30"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1573.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 2888, of the 17th ultimo, reporting that a mob has killed a
                            native hospital assistant at Chiang Pei and demolished premises rented
                            by American missionaries at that place.</p>
                        <p>Your energetic remonstrance to the Tsung-li Yamên and demand for
                            appropriate redress according to the ascertained circumstances are
                            approved by the Department.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>